<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>ASL's contents tagged with "freedom"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/asl</link><description>ASL's contents tagged with "freedom"</description><item><title>ASL supports global movement for democracy</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style="float: left; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 6px; margin-right: 6px;" alt="" src="/articles/0036/7818/adesivo-15o.jpg"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;ASL will be part of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;october, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;15 movement, which begun in Spain, claiming for a real democratic society. In several parts of the world, youngsters are gathering to demand a just society. In Porto Alegre, the gathering will be around 1:00 PM, in the Monumento do Expedicionário, in Parque Farroupilha (Redenção). The march will proceed up to Praça da Matriz, where the camp will be built. Software Livre Radio will broadcast all the works right from Praça da Matriz.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"I believe the movements from the youngsters, from digital culture, free culture, free software, free medias shall gather around this march in a global scale. The leftist parties cannot be set aside, just watching the events go by", says Marcelo Branco, freedom activist and ASL ex-coordinator.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How it all begun&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;a href="http://translate.google.com/translate?sl=pt&amp;amp;tl=en&amp;amp;js=n&amp;amp;prev=_t&amp;amp;hl=pt-BR&amp;amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;amp;layout=2&amp;amp;eotf=1&amp;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fsul21.com.br%2Fjornal%2F2011%2F10%2Fdia-mundial-de-acampamentos-em-pracas-tera-programacao-cultural-no-rs%2F"&gt;source Sul21&lt;/a&gt;, machine translated)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In the midst of the economic and politic crisis, in May, a series of protests begun to take place in Spain, results of a mobilization which begun in the Internet and took the streets of many spanish cities. The movement, called "Democracia Real Ya!" started to gain momentum over the homonym digital platform www.democraciarealya.es. In the website, they define themselves as "unemployed, badly paid, subcontracted, precarious, young".&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The first protest occurred in May 15, 2011, in the eve of local elections, with calls in 58 spanish cities. They are peaceful protests that claim for a change in politics and in spanish society. Protests keep going on, and in June, 12, it gathered 200,000 people in Puerta del Sol, in Madrid.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Oct 2011 23:52:20 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/asl/noticias/asl-supports-global-movement-for-democracy</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/asl/noticias/asl-supports-global-movement-for-democracy</guid></item></channel></rss>